5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 57, L.D. 92, “An Act Regarding the
10 Management of the Waste Components of a Solar Energy Development upon
11 Decommissioning”
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of the emergency preamble.
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3491, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2023, c. 300, §1, is further
16 amended by amending the 2nd blocked paragraph to read:
17 "Decommissioning" includes: the grading to postconstruction grade and revegetation of all
18 earth disturbed during construction and decommissioning, except for areas already
19 restored,; providing for the recycling of the waste components of the solar energy
20 development that are recyclable, including, but not limited to, the solar panels, by a facility
21 authorized to accept such materials for recycling and; providing for the disposal of the
22 waste components of the solar energy development that are not recyclable by a facility
23 authorized to accept such materials for disposal; and providing for the proper storage of the
24 waste components of the solar energy development, including, but not limited to, damaged,
25 unused or unwanted solar panels, in accordance with applicable laws and rules regulating
26 the management and storage of solid waste if the waste components do not contain
27 hazardous materials or, in accordance with applicable laws and rules regulating the
28 management and storage of hazardous waste, if the waste components contain hazardous
29 materials.'
30 Amend the bill by striking out all of the emergency clause.
31 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
32 number to read consecutively.
