COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 57, L.D. 92
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
33 removes the emergency preamble and emergency clause. It amends the solar energy
44 decommissioning laws by stipulating that the decommissioning of a solar energy
55 development includes providing for the proper storage of the waste components of the solar
66 energy development, including, but not limited to, damaged, unused or unwanted solar
77 panels, in accordance with applicable laws and rules regulating the management and
88 storage of solid waste if the waste components do not contain hazardous materials or, in
99 accordance with applicable laws and rules regulating the management and storage of
1100 hazardous waste, if the waste components contain hazardous materials.
